    "explanation": "A <span class=\"text-teal\"><span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">disk drive</span></span> is the hardware component specifically designed to <span class=\"text-green\"><span class=\"text-green font-bold\">read data from and often write data to</span></span> physical disks, such as <span class=\"text-orange\"><span class=\"text-orange font-bold\">CDs, DVDs, or Blu-ray discs</span></span>. <span class=\"text-red\"><span class=\"text-red font-bold\">Memory (RAM)</span> stores temporary data, the <span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">CPU</span> performs processing, and the ALU handles arithmetic and logic operations</span>, none of which are locations for inserting a disk.",
    "pyq": null,
