        "label": "C"
      },
      {
        "id": "d",
        "text": "All of the above",
        "label": "D"
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "<span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">Laser printers</span> operate by using a <span class=\"text-teal\"><span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">laser beam</span></span> to create an electrostatic image on a <span class=\"text-teal\"><span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">photoconductive drum</span></span>. Toner then adheres to this image and is transferred to paper, which is fused by heat. <span class=\"text-red\"><span class=\"text-red font-bold\">Print heads</span></span> are characteristic of <span class=\"text-teal\"><span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">inkjet printers</span></span>, not <span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">laser printers</span>, as <span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">laser printers</span> use an entirely different electrophotographic process.",
    "pyq": null,
    "created_at": "2026-06-15T04:34:13.034365+00:00"
