        "label": "D"
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "<span class=\"text-teal\"><span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">BIOS</span></span> (Basic Input/Output System) is <span class=\"text-green\"><span class=\"text-green font-bold\">firmware stored on a ROM</span> (Read-Only Memory) chip</span> on the motherboard. It performs the <span class=\"text-blue\"><span class=\"text-blue font-bold\">Power-On Self-Test (POST)</span></span> when the computer starts, initializing hardware and booting the operating system. <span class=\"text-red\">Unlike <span class=\"text-red font-bold\">RAM</span>, <span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">BIOS</span> instructions are <span class=\"text-red font-bold\">non-volatile</span> and persist even when power is off.</span>",
    "pyq": null,
    "created_at": "2026-06-15T04:34:13.034365+00:00"
