    "explanation": "A <span class=\"text-teal\"><span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">compiler</span></span> primarily detects <span class=\"text-green\"><span class=\"text-green font-bold\">syntax errors</span></span>, which are <span class=\"text-red\">violations of the programming language's <span class=\"text-red font-bold\">grammatical rules</span></span> (e.g., missing semicolons). It can also identify some <span class=\"text-orange\">semantic errors</span> like type mismatches. <span class=\"text-red\"><span class=\"text-red font-bold\">Logical errors</span>, however, are not detectable by the <span class=\"text-teal font-bold\">compiler</span></span> as they pertain to program behavior, not its structure, and require <span class=\"text-green font-bold\">runtime debugging</span>.",
